### Key Findings

- **Tailwind v4 `@theme` fix is 2 lines**: Change `--color-primary: #c3c0ff` and `--color-primary-container: #4F46E5` in `frontend/src/index.css`. Because `.gradient-cta` already uses `var(--color-primary-container)` and `var(--color-primary)`, the gradient corrects automatically with no further changes.
- **Inter font**: Add two preconnect hints (`fonts.googleapis.com` + `fonts.gstatic.com crossorigin`) and one Google Fonts `<link>` tag early in `index.html`'s `<head>`. Then prepend `'Inter'` to the `font-family` stack in `body {}`.
- **GraphView.tsx `#4F46E5` hardcodes don't need changing**: Canvas-rendered colors can't reference CSS variables. After the token fix, `#4F46E5` correctly maps to `primary-container` (indigo fill for task/note nodes) — the values remain semantically accurate.

### Gaps

- Design reference HTML files (`design/*/code.html`) contain hardcoded colors but are not production source — no functional impact either way.

Sources:
- [Theme variables — Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme)
- [Color roles — Material Design 3](https://m3.material.io/styles/color/roles)
- [Best practices for fonts — web.dev](https://web.dev/articles/font-best-practices)
- [Faster Google Fonts with Preconnect — CDN Planet](https://www.cdnplanet.com/blog/faster-google-webfonts-preconnect/)
