## Investigation Complete

**Issue**: #697 — Design tokens: fix primary / primary-container color inversion and load Inter font
**Type**: ENHANCEMENT

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Priority | HIGH | Inverted tokens corrupt every `text-primary`, `bg-primary`, `gradient-cta` usage app-wide |
| Complexity | LOW | Changes to 2 files only; GraphView canvas colors are already semantically correct post-fix |
| Confidence | HIGH | Root cause is unambiguous — token values are literally swapped vs DESIGN.md spec |

### Key Findings

- **Root Cause**: Commit `04c722b` introduced `--color-primary: #4F46E5` and `--color-primary-container: #3730A3` — exactly reversed from `design/reli_obsidian/DESIGN.md` which specifies `primary = #c3c0ff` (lavender) and `primary-container = #4F46E5` (indigo)
- **gradient-cta** currently renders `#3730A3 → #4F46E5` (purple-to-indigo); should be `#4F46E5 → #c3c0ff` (indigo-to-lavender)
- **GraphView.tsx** hardcodes `#4F46E5` for canvas nodes — no change needed; it correctly represents `primary-container` after the fix
- **Inter font**: not in `index.html` and missing from font-family stack in `index.css:52`

### Files to Modify

| File | Action |
|------|--------|
| `frontend/src/index.css:20-21` | Fix token values |
| `frontend/src/index.css:52` | Add `'Inter'` to font stack |
| `frontend/index.html` | Add Inter Google Fonts preconnect + link |

